%20to%20any%20significant%20extent%20makes%20us%20believe%20that%20it%20is%20completely%20locked%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20like%20Tobin%20fear%20that%20without%20releasing%20tension%20through%20smaller%20earthquakes%2C%20the%20Cascadia%20subduction%20zone%20is%20more%20likely%20to%20erupt%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bmegathrust%26quot%3B%20earthquake%20%E2%80%94%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-one-mega-earthquake-what-will-happen-california-san-andreas-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emegaquake%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20short%20%E2%80%94%20with%20a%20magnitude%20of%20about%209.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20will%20be%20the%20worst%20natural%20disaster%20our%20country%20has%20ever%20seen%2C%26quot%3B%20Ezelle%20said.%20That's%20why%20some%20call%20it%20the%20%26quot%3BBig%20One.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20the%20Cascadia%20subduction%20zone%20produces%20an%20immense%20earthquake%20every%20200%20to%20500%20years.%20The%20most%20recent%20one%20was%20in%201700.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fd9980cd-d7a5-43d2-a20d-8773726b7cbb%5C%22%3EJust%20how%20big%20is%20the%20Big%20One%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222290%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ocean%20bean%20with%20dead%20tree%20stumps%20in%20the%20water%20and%20a%20large%20rock%20with%20trees%20on%20it%20in%20the%20distance%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671ab28401ea6d83dee3f2c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20%26quot%3Bghost%20forest%26quot%3B%20of%20Sitka%20spruces%20juts%20up%20from%20an%20Oregon%20beach.%20The%20trees%20were%20likely%20buried%20by%20tsunami%20debris%20in%201700.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FAndrew%20Selsky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Richter%20scale%2C%20which%20measures%20earthquake%20magnitude%2C%20is%20logarithmic%2C%20not%20linear.%20That%20means%20a%20magnitude%209%20quake%20releases%20about%2032%20times%20as%20muc