ases%20until%20after%20November%205%2C%20according%20to%20a%20September%20survey%20of%20400%20Kroger%20shoppers%20by%2084.51%2C%20the%20grocer's%20marketing%20subsidiary.%20Eighteen%20percent%20of%20those%20surveyed%20said%20they%20were%20holding%20off%20on%20buying%20big-ticket%20items%20such%20as%20electronics%20or%20appliances.%20Slightly%20smaller%20percentages%20said%20they%20were%20holding%20off%20on%20an%20investment%20decision%20or%20buying%20a%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20might%20be%20holding%20off%20on%20big%20purchases%20because%20they%20need%20loans%20and%20hope%20that%20interest%20rates%20will%20fall%20more%20in%20the%20months%20after%20the%20election%2C%20said%20Alex%20Trott%2C%20director%20of%20insights%20at%2084.51.%20But%20some%20might%20not%20actually%20care%20as%20much%20about%20the%20election%20as%20the%20seasonal%20promotions%20that%20tend%20to%20follow%20in%20November%20and%20December%2C%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20also%20bumping%20up%20against%20a%20holiday%20season%20where%20there%20are%20always%20sales%2C%26quot%3B%20Trott%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20under%2034%20were%20also%20more%20likely%20than%20older%20consumers%20to%20put%20off%20a%20major%20financial%20commitment%20until%20after%20the%20election%2C%2084.51%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOlder%20consumers%2C%20such%20as%20Baby%20Boomers%20and%20members%20of%20Gen%20X%2C%20%26quot%3Bcan%20make%20some%20of%20these%20bigger%20decisions%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Trott.%20%26quot%3BYounger%20people%20don't%20have%20that%20spending%20power.%20They%20are%20sensitive%20to%20these%20smaller%20price%20changes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20%E2%80%94%2053%25%2C%20according%20to%2084.51%20%E2%80%94%20said%20they%20weren't%20delaying%20any%20big%20purchases%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20US%20election%20is%20taking%20place%20after%20years%20of%20inflation%20have%20squeezed%20consumers.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpennsylvania-groce