ily%20on%20federal%20government%20income%2C%20mainly%20through%20Social%20Security%20and%20Medicare%2C%20with%20two%20rural%20counties%20%E2%80%94%20Fayette%20and%20Cambria%20%E2%80%94%20among%20the%20most%20reliant%20in%20the%20nation%2C%20a%20report%20from%20the%20bipartisan%20Economic%20Innovation%20Group%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F3HSJp%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Share%20of%20population%20age%2065%20and%20over%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22444%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EBenjamin%20Glasner%2C%20a%20coauthor%20of%20EIG's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feig.org%2Fgreat-transfermation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20most%20reliant%20counties%20were%20generally%20in%20older%2C%20poor%2C%20and%20more%20rural%20communities.%20Cambria%2C%20for%20example%2C%20needed%20more%20government%20aid%20after%20steel%20plant%20closures%20in%20the%201980s.%20Residents'%20incomes%20still%20haven't%20recovered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20only%20receive%20so%20much%20from%20Social%20Security.%20Medicare%20can%20only%20cover%20so%20much%2C%20and%20Medicaid%20can%20only%20cover%20so%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20Glasner%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20creates%20%26quot%3Ba%20thin%20level%20of%20economic%20prosperity%26quot%3B%20reliant%20on%20the%20program's%20generosity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20Crossey%2C%2073%2C%20has%20seen%20the%20limits%20of%20government%20aid%20firsthand%20in%20his%20work%20as%20an%20advocate%20for%20retirees.%20The%20Pittsburgh-area%20resident%20wants%20the%20next%20president%20of%20the%20US%20to%20strengthen%20Social%20Security%2C%20protect%20pensions%2C%20and%20expand%20Medicare.%20He%20said%20he%20knows%20too%20many%20older%20Americans%20who%20live%20off%20Social%20Security%20alone%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fpolicy%2Fdocs%2Fquickfacts%2Fstat_snapshot%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaveraged%3C%2Fa%3E%20%241%2C921%20nationally%20for%20retirees%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20run%20into%20people%20every%20day%20who%20are%20still%20making%20decisions%20about%2C%20'Do%20I%20take%20my%20prescriptions%20today%20or%20do%20I%20have%20lunch%20today%3F'%20And%20that%20just%20breaks%20my%20heart%2C%26quot%3B%20Crossey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Trump%20has%20denied%20that%20he%20would%20cut%20Social%20Security%20and%20previously%20criticized%20GOP%20lawmakers%20who%20proposed%20raising%20the%20retirement%20age%20to%2070%2C%20the%20Committee%20for%20a%20Responsible%20Budget%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crfb.org%2Fblogs%2Fwhat-would-trump-campaign-plans-mean-social-security%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Trump's%20policies%20could%20force%20cuts%20to%20Social%20Security%20benefits%20in%20as%20little%20as%20six%20years.%20Harris%20has%20proposed%20strengthening%20Social%20Security%20by%20ensuring%20the%20wealthy%20and%20big%20corporations%20pay%20what%20they%20owe%20in%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20Social%20Security%20and%20Medicare%20Board%20of%20Trustees%20report%20recently%20projecting%20that%20Social%20Security%20will%20only%20be%20able%20to%20pay%20out%20full%20benefits%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-social-security-benefits-run-out-retirement-crisis-boomers-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor%20the%20next%2011%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20issue%20is%20growing%20more%20pressing%2C%20and%20not%20only%20for%20Pennsylvanians.%20Richard%20Fiesta%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20nonpartisan%204%20million-member%20Alliance%20for%20Retired%20Americans%2C%20said%20that%20%26quot%3BCongress%20and%20the%20next%20administration%20needs%20to%20have%20a%20serious%20look%20at%20Social%20Security.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20retirees%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-401k-pension-real-estate-investments-baby-boomers-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eable%20to%20live%20comfortably%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20economic%20headwinds.%20However%2C%20Fiesta%20said%20the%20decline%20in%20defined%20benefit%20pension%20plans%2C%20or%20employer-subsidized%20retirement%20plans%2C%20contributes%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-crisis-social-security-poverty-older-americans-savings-inequality-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslump%20in%20average%20retiree%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20that%20more%20and%20more%20Americans%20rely%20primarily%20on%20Social%20Security%20to%20help%20keep%20them%20financially%20afloat%20as%20they%20age.%20The%20previously%20mentioned%20EIG%20report%20found%20that%20income%20from%20government%20aid%20is%20the%20fastest-growing%20portion%20of%20an%20American's%20income%2C%20and%20it%20is%20primarily%20driven%20by%20retirees%2C%20who%20make%20up%20a%20rising%20share%20of%20the%20total%20US%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20we're%20just%20kind%20of%20seeing%20that%20now%20over%20the%20last%2010%20to%2015%20years%20as%20that%20generation%20ages%20into%20retirement%2C%26quot%3B%20Fiesta%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a2e550dc-625f-4039-8e34-cbb0ecc4d25f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20aging%20workforce%20creates%20job%20mismatches%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20workforce%20in%20Pennsylvania%20is%20already%20starting%20to%20see%20imbalances%20as%20the%20younger%20population%20dwindles%20and%20the%20number%20of%20retirees%20grows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKyle%20Kopko%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20bipartisan%20legislative%20agency%20Center%20for%20Rural%20Pennsylvania%2C%20said%20local%20business%20owners%20complain%20of%20labor%20shortages.%20CRP%20research%20suggests%20that's%20due%20to%20fewer%20older%20adults%20working%20traditional%20jobs%20and%20instead%20pursuing%20entrepreneurship%20to%20supplement%20their%20retirement%20incomes.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20lower%20birth%20rates%20mean%20younger%20adults%20are%20not%20filling%20the%20open%20roles%20either%2C%20Kopko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20pool%20of%20younger%20adults%20in%20Pennsylvania%20who%20can%20backfill%20for%20some%20of%20the%20retirees%2C%20that's%20going%20to%20create%20supply%20and%20demand%20imbalances%2C%26quot%3B%20Kopko%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20role%20retirees%20play%20in%20the%20economy%20as%20consumers%2C%20but%20less%20so%20as%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20jobs%20nationwide%2C%20Harris%20proposed%20tax%20incentives%20for%20small%20businesses%20to%20spur%20more%20hiring%2C%20while%20Trump%20has%20largely%20focused%20on%20bolstering%20manufacturing%20in%20the%20US%20to%20create%20more%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20possible%20avenue%20for%20job%20creation%20%E2%80%94%20the%20infrastructure%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20has%20hardly%20been%20mentioned%20by%20either%20candidate%20in%20policy%20discussions.%20Bill%20Candelori%2C%20a%2068-year-old%20retired%20commercial%20painter%2C%20sees%20this%20as%20an%20overlooked%20opportunity.%20He%20says%20Biden's%20infrastructure%20investments%2C%20which%20brought%20%2416%20billion%20to%20Pennsylvania%2C%20was%20a%20promising%20step%20but%20wants%20the%20next%20administration%20to%20go%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20only%20roads%20and%20bridges.%20It's%20airports%2C%20it's%20water%20authorities%2C%20it's%20schools%2C%20it's%20libraries%2C%20any%20public%20project%2C%26quot%3B%20Candelori%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20work%20for%20us.%20And%20it's%20work%20afterward%20on%20maintaining%20those%20facilities.%20It's%20job%20creation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22485b4799-3267-4ca3-96b7-d90ae5f90405%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolitical%20steps%20being%20taken%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EState%20and%20local%20governments%20have%20already%20taken%20steps%20to%20address%20these%20mounting%20issues.%20Pennsylvania%20Gov.%20Josh%20Shapiro%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Democrat%20%E2%80%94%20has%20worked%20with%20members%20of%20his%20administration%20to%20create%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pa.gov%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Fcopapwp-pagov%2Fen%2Faging%2Fdocuments%2Faging-our-way%2Fdocuments%2FAOW%2520Final%2520PDF%2520online%2520version%2520with%2520signature.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E10-year%20strategic%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20outlined%20eight%20key%20priorities%20for%20older%20adults%2C%20including%20housing%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20health%20and%20community%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPennsylvania's%20Aging%20Secretary%20Jason%20Kavulich%20said%20it's%20a%20bipartisan%20issue%20that%20has%20bipartisan%20support%3A%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20not%20a%20representative%20or%20senator%20who%20I've%20ever%20sat%20down%20with%20that%20does%20not%20care%20about%20older%20adults%20in%20their%20district.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJR%20Reed%20and%20Krista%20Geer%2C%20both%20in%20charge%20of%20county-wide%20aging%20agencies%2C%20have%20met%20with%20older%20adults%20in%20Pennsylvania%20to%20hear%20their%20top%20worries.%20Geer%20said%20that%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20concerns%20she's%20heard%20about%20is%20the%20high%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20which%20has%20interfered%20with%20their%20ability%20to%20afford%20medications%2C%20gas%2C%20and%20groceries.%20Though%20inflation%20has%20moderated%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20it's%20still%20historically%20elevated%20and%20putting%20pressure%20on%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSocial%20security%20just%20doesn't%20quite%20keep%20pace%20with%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Geer%20said.%20The%20program%20adjusts%20payouts%20annually%20to%20account%20for%20inflation.%20Critics%20say%20it%20isn't%20tied%20to%20a%20measure%20that%20accurately%20reflects%20the%20spending%20of%20older%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReed%20and%20Geer%20agree%20the%20solution%20is%20for%20older%20populations%20to%20have%20a%20bigger%20nest%20egg%2C%20but%20not%20one%20that%20comes%20from%20Social%20Security.%20Reed%20said%20that%20he%20hopes%20Trump%20or%20Harris%20will%20continue%20to%20fund%20a%201965%20federal%20law%20that%20provides%20funding%20to%20states%20to%20better%20support%20older%20adults.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20federal%20level%2C%20Harris%20recently%20proposed%20a%20plan%20that%20would%20allow%20Medicare%20coverage%20for%20in-home%20eldercare%2C%20which%20Fiesta%20said%20would%20%26quot%3Bgo%20a%20long%20way%26quot%3B%20toward%20helping%20both%20older%20adults%20and%20the%20family%20members%20who%20typically%20would%20take%20care%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%2C%20to%20date%2C%20has%20offered%20minimal%20details%20about%20his%20plans%20to%20address%20eldercare.%20Brian%20Hughes%20%E2%80%94%20his%20campaign's%20senior%20advisor%20%E2%80%94%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20presidential%20hopeful%20and%20his%20running%20mate%2C%20JD%20Vance%2C%20%26quot%3Bshare%20the%20principles%20of%20using%20more%20choice%20in%20the%20marketplace%20and%20efficiency%20as%20tools%20for%20better%2C%20more%20affordable%20health%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20stakes%20for%20an%20aging%20US%20population%20are%20high%2C%20and%20bipartisan%20participation%20is%20required%20to%20ensure%20the%20country%20is%20properly%20prepared%20for%20a%20surge%20in%20retirees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKavulich%20said%20that%20the%20shift%20needs%20to%20be%20addressed%20head-on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOlder%20adults%20really%20drive%20our%20economies%2C%26quot%3B%20Kavulich%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20drive%20our%20communities%2C%20and%20we%20have%20to%20respect%20that.%20And%20we%20have%20to%20not%20just%20think%20of%20them%20as%20frail%20and%20old%20and%20vulnerable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20o